# =============================================================================
# .dockerignore — what NOT to copy into the Docker build context
# =============================================================================
# WHAT: Tells `docker build` to skip these files when assembling the image.
# WHY:  (1) Speed — smaller context = faster `COPY .` instructions.
#       (2) Security — `.env*` files contain secrets and must never end up
#           inside the image (which gets pushed to a registry).
#       (3) Correctness — host node_modules are wrong arch (likely Win/Mac);
#           image installs fresh Linux modules.
#
# IMPORTANT: this file affects `docker build` only. It does NOT affect what
# docker-compose mounts via `volumes:` — Compose reads .env.local at runtime
# from the host. Both rules co-exist.
# =============================================================================

# dependencies (reinstalled inside container)
node_modules
.pnp
.pnp.js

# build output (rebuilt inside container)
.next
out
build

# git history
.git
.gitignore

# tests / coverage (not needed in image)
coverage
.jest-cache
tests
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx

# env files (secrets — must NEVER ship in the image)
.env*
!.env.example

# local docker overrides
docker-compose.override.yml

# IDE / OS junk
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*.swp

# logs
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*

# docs (don't bloat the image)
docs
README.md
*.md

# Sentry config (auth token must not ship)
sentry.properties
